    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An acquired defect of cellular immunity associated with infection by species of human immunodeficiency viruses. Criteria as defined by the CDC in 1993 include a CD4-positive T-lymphocyte count under 200 cells/microliter or less than 14% of total lymphocytes, and increased susceptibility to opportunistic infections and malignant neoplasms. Clinical manifestations also include emaciation and dementia. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
